The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Hospital drug racket
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      Hospital drug racket
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	The CBI arrested four people and seized a large quantity of spurious drugs from hospitals and dispensaries across the city and the districts over the past week. An officer said the raids revealed a nexus between pharmaceutical companies, traders and hospital employees.         
	The sleuths also raided petrol pumps and oil depots across the state following complaints of adulteration.         
	Boy death: The relatives of a two-year-old boy who was declared dead at TL Jaiswal Hospital in Howrah early on Thursday demonstrated on the premises later in the day alleging that Shyam Projapati died after being administered polio, DPT and Hepatitis B vaccines in the outpatients department the previous morning. They said he fell ill late on Wednesday. Swati Dutta, the chief medical officer of health, Howrah, has ordered an inquiry into the incident.         
	Suicides: A 47-year-old man was found hanging from the ceiling in his Chitpur home on Thursday morning. Sambhu Sen was taken to RG Kar hospital where he was declared dead. Relatives said Sen was suffering from depression.         
	At Sinthee, Binita Ghoshal, a first-year college student, was found hanging from the ceiling in her bedroom. Binita was struggling to cope with her studies, said family members.         
	Aircraft snag: Passengers of a Calcutta-Bhubaneswar Jetlite flight were offloaded after a snag was detected in the aircraft on Thursday. The flight was to take off at 7.30pm. The fliers boarded a second flight, which also developed a snag. The flight finally left at 10pm.         
